.TH A2WCRECALC 1 "2026-07-05" "a2tools 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
a2wcrecalc \- recalculate Apache configs to toggle wildcard subdomain support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B a2wcrecalc
.RI [ wildcard\-domain ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBa2wcrecalc\fR walks every Apache site config under
\fB/etc/apache2/sites\-available/\fR and rewrites the \fBServerName\fR /
\fBServerAlias\fR directives so that the wildcard subdomain (default
\fBmail.*\fR, configurable via the first argument) is either added or
removed from each vhost consistently.
.PP
This is the safe way to enable or disable wildcard subdomains across all
existing vhosts: it preserves the rest of the config, only touching the
server name lines, and re\-enables / disables the affected site
symlinks under \fBsites\-enabled\fR.
.PP
After the rewrite, run
.RB \fBapache2ctl configtest\fR
and
.RB \fBsystemctl reload apache2\fR
to apply.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I wildcard\-domain
Optional. Subdomain wildcard pattern to add or remove (default
\fBmail.*\fR).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apache2/sites\-available/
Apache vhost configs.
.TP
.I /etc/apache2/sites\-enabled/
Symlinks to enabled vhosts.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR a2sitemgr (1),
.BR a2wcrecalc\-dms (1),
.BR apache2ctl (8)
